[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A libFuzzer run aborted due to a timeout. The fuzzer did not complete within the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         allotted time window, indicating that during one of its test inputs the target code [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         hung or entered a long-running state rather than producing a normal exit, crash, or [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         sanitizer report.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue Overview                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The fuzzer execution terminated with an error message “ERROR: libFuzzer:          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         timeout.” No crash, sanitizer alert, or exception was reported; instead, the        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         process exceeded the configured time limit and was forcefully stopped.              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability Type                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           While no explicit security vulnerability was triggered [1m([0me.g., buffer overflow or  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         use-after-free[1m)[0m, the symptom corresponds to a denial-of-service [1m([0mDoS[1m)[0m or hang       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         condition. Under certain inputs, the code under test fails to make forward progress [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or enters a prolonged execution path.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Important Observations and Findings                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The timeout originates from libFuzzer’s watchdog monitoring mechanism.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The fuzzer observed an input that caused either an infinite loop, blocking I/O, [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         heavy computation, or deadlock.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • No memory-sanitizer or undefined-behavior sanitizer findings accompanied the    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         timeout.                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The harness served solely as the entry point; it forwarded fuzzer-generated     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         data to the target functions without additional instrumentation or checks.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code Areas to Investigate                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. **Target Functions and Input Parsers**: Any API or parsing routines that       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         consume the raw byte sequences provided by the harness—especially loops, recursive  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         callbacks, or state machines.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. **Synchronization Primitives**: If the code uses locks, mutexes, condition     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         variables, or other thread-safety constructs, verify for potential deadlocks or     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indefinite waits.                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. **Blocking Operations**: I/O calls [1m([0mfile, network, or device[1m)[0m or waits on      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         external resources that might not return promptly under unexpected inputs.          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. **Performance Hotspots**: Computational routines that could degrade            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exponentially on particular inputs [1m([0me.g., pathological combinatorial cases[1m)[0m.        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m5[0m. **Harness-to-Code Interface**: Although not the root cause, review how the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         harness invokes the library’s entry points and ensures timely return [1m([0mfor example,  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         discard calls that spin indefinitely without a timeout[1m)[0m.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m6[0m. **Library Dependencies**: Any third-party or external modules invoked by the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         code under test, which may themselves block or loop under certain inputs.           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A thorough review of these areas, correlating the fuzzer’s last inputs and coverage [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         feedback, will provide a holistic view of why execution exceeded the permitted time [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         budget.                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m309[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m read trailing bytes into buffer[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m310[0m[39m:        try[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m311[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m312[0m[39m:            final int trailByteCount = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileLen < readTrailBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m[1;39m([0m[39mint[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfileLen : readTrailBytes;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m313[0m[39m:            buf = new byte[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mtrailByteCount[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m314[0m[39m:            skipBytes = fileLen - trailByteCount;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m315[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[39mskipBytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m316[0m[39m:            int off = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m317[0m[39m:            int readBytes;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m318[0m[39m:            while [0m[1;39m([0m[39moff < trailByteCount[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m319[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m320[0m[39m:                readBytes = [0m[1;35msource.read[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbuf, off, trailByteCount - off[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m321[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m in order to not get stuck in a loop we check readBytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthis[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould never happen[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m322[0m[39m:                if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreadBytes < [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m323[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m324[0m[39m:                    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m325[0m[39m:                            [0m[32m"No more bytes to read for trailing buffer, but [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mexpected: "[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m326[0m[39m:                                    + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrailByteCount - off[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m327[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m328[0m[39m:                off += readBytes;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m329[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m330[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m331[0m[39m:        finally[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m332[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m333[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35msource.seek[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m335[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m find last [0m[32m'%%EOF'[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m336[0m[39m:        int bufOff = [0m[1;35mlastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER, buf, buf.length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m337[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbufOff < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m338[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m339[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39misLenient[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m340[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m341[0m[39m:                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m in lenient mode the [0m[32m'%%EOF'[0m[39m isn't needed[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m342[0m[39m:                bufOff = buf.length;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m343[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35mLOG.debug[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Missing end of file marker '[0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m'"[0m[39m, new [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m344[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m345[0m[39m:            else [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m346[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m347[0m[39m:                throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Missing end of file marker '"[0m[39m + new [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mEOF_MARKER[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[32m"'"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m348[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m349[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m350[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m find last startxref preceding EOF marker[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m351[0m[39m:        bufOff = [0m[1;35mlastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSTARTXREF, buf, bufOff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m352[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbufOff < [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m353[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m354[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Missing 'startxref' marker."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m355[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m356[0m[39m:        else[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m357[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m358[0m[39m:            return skipBytes + bufOff;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m359[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m360[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Limit and Validate Cross-Reference Entry Counts in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mXrefParser.parseXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Locate the `[0m[1;35mparseXrefTable[0m[1;39m([0m[39mlong start[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in `XrefParser` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m250[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This method reads two numbers—`firstObjectNumber` and `count`—via [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mparser.readNumber[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, then loops `count` times to read each xref entry. Because [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`count` comes from untrusted PDF data, a maliciously large `count` can drive an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munbounded or very long loop, causing the observed timeout.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Introduce a validation step immediately after reading `count`:  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Compute a safe upper‐bound for `count` based on the PDF’s length, e.g.:  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        `maxEntries = fileLength [0m[35m/[0m[39m MIN_BYTES_PER_XREF_ENTRY` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MIN_BYTES_PER_XREF_ENTRY` is a conservative estimate, e.g., [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes per entry[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `count` exceeds `maxEntries` or a hard‐coded threshold [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrow an `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupt xref table: too many entries [0m[32m([0m[32mcount[0m[32m="[0m[39m + count + [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. This prevents extremely large or negative counts from triggering lengthy [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Bound the “PREV” Chained Xref Loop**  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In the `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprev > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && prev != lastPrev[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` loop within `[0m[1;35mparseXref[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, add [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma maximum iteration counter [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `int chainDepth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` and `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++chainDepth > [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_XREF_CHAIN_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupt xref chain: too many [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32msubsections"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. This guard prevents pathological “Prev” loops or extremely long chains of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincremental xref sections.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Cap Brute-Force Object Scanning in BruteForceParser**  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Identify the `[0m[1;35mbfSearchForObjects[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in `BruteForceParser`. It scans [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe entire file byte-by-byte searching for “obj” markers, which on large or [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed inputs can take an excessive amount of time.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Introduce a maximum searchable byte limit, e.g., `long maxScan = [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mMath.min[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileLength, MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SCAN_BYTES[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SCAN_BYTES` might be [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Stop scanning once `currentOffset >= [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxScan`, and if not enough objects were found to build a valid xref table, throw [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Insufficient objects found in brute-force parse; aborting"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Optionally, also limit the number of objects collected [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., cap at [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m000[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjects[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fail Fast for Malformed Trailers**  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Although `[0m[1;35mgetStartxrefOffset[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` already bounds its search by [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`readTrailBytes`, ensure `readTrailBytes` is not excessively large. Verify in the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstructor of `COSParser` that `readTrailBytes` is a small constant [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ≤ [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. If `readTrailBytes` were exposed for customization, restrict it to a safe [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximum.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Unit Tests and Backward Compatibility**  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Add unit tests on small synthetic PDFs that declare absurdly large xref [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounts or extremely deep `Prev` chains to verify that the parser now fails fast [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith the expected `IOException`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Ensure existing valid PDFs still parse correctly by testing against [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mknown-good sample files.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. All new code paths only add early-exit checks; they do not alter normal [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing logic or existing API behavior when inputs are within expected bounds.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Justification & Side-Effect Mitigation**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By validating the xref entry `count` and capping chain depth, we directly address[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe DoS hang symptom caused by unbounded loops in `XrefParser`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Limiting brute-force scanning prevents prolonged byte-by-byte searching in [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BruteForceParser`, which is a fallback path only used when PDFs are malformed.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- All bounds are derived from either file length or conservative hard-coded limits,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring legitimate but large PDFs still succeed.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throwing `IOException` on exceeding limits is consistent with existing error [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msignaling in the parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., missing markers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effects [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfalse positives on extremely large but valid PDFs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can be[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigated by tuning `MAX_*` thresholds or providing a parser configuration flag for[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhigh-volume workloads—without exposing fuzz harness or requiring external [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependency changes.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This strategy preserves existing functionality, does not modify harness or tests,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand confines patches to targeted loops in the core parser code.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/23/25 13:12:10][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=709063;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=397799;file:///home/user/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0mn evals: [1;36m2[0m, patch status: PatchStatus.VULNERABLE[1m)[0m                                   [2m               [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    referencedObject = [0m[1;35mparseFileObject[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffsetOrObjstmObNr, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobjKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                else[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m xref value is object nr of object stream containing object [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto be parsed[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    referencedObject = [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mparseObjectStreamObject[0m[1;39m([0m[39m-offsetOrObjstmObNr, objKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreferencedObject == null || referencedObject instanceof COSNull[0m[1;39m)[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m not defined object -> NULL object[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;35mpdfObject.setToNull[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return referencedObject;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        finally[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            parseDepth--;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn ongoing libFuzzer run against the PDFBox codebase is terminating with a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“timeout” error, indicating that some inputs cause the parser to run indefinitely [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor exceed the fuzzer’s time budget. To address potential infinite loops in [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcross-reference table parsing and excessive scanning during brute-force recovery, a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was proposed. The patch adds:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In XrefParser: a maximum chain depth counter [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMAX_XREF_CHAIN_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrows an IOException if exceeded.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In BruteForceParser: a maximum scan byte limit [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SCAN_BYTES = [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMB[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and throws an IOException when the scan exceeds this threshold.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite applying this patch, the fuzzer still reports “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout,” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating the issue persists.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness invokes PDFBox parsing routines and eventually the run exceeds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer’s timeout threshold.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The only observable symptom in the logs is “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout,” with no [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccompanying exception traces from the code under test.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey Observations  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The timeout implies unbounded processing on certain malformed or adversarial [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No stack traces or exceptions were emitted—likely because the code never reaches [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man error-throwing condition or blocks in internal loops.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness itself simply drives the parser; it does not impose limits on parser [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops beyond libFuzzer’s overall timeout.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. In `XrefParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m98[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a local `chainDepth` counter initialized to [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Defined `final int MAX_XREF_CHAIN_DEPTH = [0m[1;36m50[0m[39m`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - On each iteration of the while-loop that follows `prev` links, increment [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`chainDepth` and throw `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupt xref chain: too many subsections [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m([0m[32m...[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if `chainDepth` exceeds the maximum.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. In `BruteForceParser.java` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m134[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Defined `final long MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SCAN_BYTES = 10L * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Computed `maxScan` as the lesser of the last EOF marker position [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif present[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB limit, or the [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m MB limit if no EOF marker.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Before each read in the brute-force loop, compared `currentOffset` to [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`maxScan`; if exceeded, threw `[0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Insufficient objects found in [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mbrute-force parse; aborting after scanning "[0m[39m + maxScan + [0m[32m" bytes"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and rerunning libFuzzer against the patched code, the only [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutput remains “ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout.”  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No new exceptions from the added checks appear in the fuzzer output, suggesting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meither the new limits are not reached on the problematic paths or other unbounded [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode paths exist.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Handling of streamed objects and incremental updates—any unbounded or poorly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimited loops there.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error-handling paths where exceptions may be caught and suppressed, leading to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msilent infinite loops.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview and Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer timeouts persist because unbounded loops and recursion remain in [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkey PDFBox parsing routines beyond XrefParser and BruteForceParser. Specifically:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a. Xref object‐stream parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparseXrefObjStream → PDFXrefStreamParser.parse[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlacks any cap on the number of entries processed.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b. Dynamic object resolution [0m[1;39m([0m[39mCOSParser.parseObjectDynamically → [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparseFileObject → parseDirObject[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can recurse arbitrarily deep on crafted [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindirect‐object graphs.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     c. Low‐level whitespace skipping [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBaseParser.skipSpaces[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and stream parsing [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmay scan large regions without bound.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The prior chain-depth and scan-bytes guards did not cover these paths, so the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser still performs unbounded work on malicious inputs.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Introduce Bounds Without Breaking Functionality[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Limit Xref Stream Entries[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In PDFXrefStreamParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere cross‐reference stream entries are read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduce:[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A `static final long MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES = 50_000;`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A local `long entryCount = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` before looping over entries.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · At the top of each iteration: `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++entryCount > [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Corrupt xref stream: too many [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mentries [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + entryCount + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Rationale: stops pathological xref‐streams that declare huge [0m[35m/[0m[95mSize[0m[39m or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontain extra garbage entries.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Cap Object‐Parse Recursion Depth[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In COSParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand BaseParser.parseDirObject call sites[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A parser‐instance field `private int parseDepth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A constant `private static final int MAX_PARSE_DEPTH = 1_000;`[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Wrap every entry into `parseDirObject`, `parseObjectDynamically`, and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseFileObject` with:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++parseDepth > MAX_PARSE_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Exceeded maximum parsing depth [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX_PARSE_DEPTH + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m original parsing logic[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m finally [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            parseDepth--;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Rationale: prevents infinite or extremely deep recursion when malicious [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobject graphs self-reference or nest deeply.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Bound Whitespace Skips[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In [0m[1;35mBaseParser.skipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A local `long skipped = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · A constant `static final long MAX_SKIP_BYTES = [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m1024[0m[39m; [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m 5MB`[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        · Within the skip loop: after reading each whitespace byte, `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m++skipped [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m> MAX_SKIP_BYTES[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Too many whitespace bytes skipped [0m[32m([0m[32m"[0m[39m + [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mskipped + [0m[32m"[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Rationale: protects against files filled with whitespace or control [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacters that would otherwise cause prolonged scanning.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Verify Brute-Force Scan Limit[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Ensure the existing MAX_BRUTE_FORCE_SCAN_BYTES logic in [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBruteForceParser.bfSearchForObjects is correctly applied to the loop condition as [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell as inside the loop:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - Update the `do [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m while` to `while [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!endOfObjFound && currentOffset <=[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaxScan[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Rationale: makes the scan‐bytes bound both preemptive and loop‐terminating.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Functionality[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All new limits are set high enough not to impact well‐formed PDFs: typical PDF[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructures have fewer than 50K xref entries, recursion depth under 1K, and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhitespace sequences shorter than 5MB.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Exceptions remain `IOException`, matching existing error contracts, so [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting catch blocks and error‐reporting are preserved.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No changes to harness, tests, or public APIs; only internal parser behavior is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtightened.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate but extremely complex PDFs [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., object streams with >50K entries[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwill now error out; users can tune constants if needed.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The recursion cap must be set so that ordinary PDFs parse fully; if clients [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mencounter false positives, they can raise `MAX_PARSE_DEPTH`.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Thorough regression tests should be run on large PDF samples to validate no [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbreakages.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Similar Patterns in Codebase[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The MAX_XREF_CHAIN_DEPTH guard in XrefParser provides precedent for per‐loop [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry limits.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The brute‐force scan limit shows how to bound scanning operations by byte [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We reuse these patterns to systematically harden all unbounded loops and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursion in the parsing stack.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/PDFXrefStreamParser.java:[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Define `MAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES`, add `entryCount` guard in `[0m[1;35mparse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequivalent loop.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. In pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/COSParser.java [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBaseParser where parseDirObject lives[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Add `int parseDepth` field and `MAX_PARSE_DEPTH` constant.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Wrap calls to `parseDirObject`, `parseObjectDynamically`, and [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`parseFileObject` with depth checks and try/finally decrement.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BaseParser.java:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Enhance `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with `MAX_SKIP_BYTES` and skip‐count guard.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In pdfbox/src/main/java/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfparser/BruteForceParser.java:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Adjust loop end condition to include `currentOffset <= maxScan`.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Run full PDFBox test suite plus targeted fuzz runs to confirm no new timeouts[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand verify existing PDF compatibility.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpathological cases that could lead to hangs or excessive work, a patch was proposed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added entry-count limits in `PDFXrefStreamParser` to guard against oversized XRef[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstreams.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced a `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method in `BaseParser` to bound whitespace skipping.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Constrained the scanning loop in `BruteForceParser` with the existing `maxScan` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlimit.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added a recursion-depth counter in `COSParser` to prevent unbounded nested [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen the patch was applied, the build immediately failed with over [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m “illegal [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of expression” and “class, interface, or enum expected” errors in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`BaseParser.java` and `BruteForceParser.java`, indicating that the diff likely [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmis-placed or unbalanced braces and left methods or statements outside of class [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbodies.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Symptom: `ERROR: libFuzzer: timeout`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Context: Under fuzz testing, certain malformed or adversarial PDFs caused the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser code to run for too long, triggering the fuzzer’s built-in timeout.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No stack trace or Java exception—just a hang until libFuzzer kills the run.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The issue occurs deep in the PDF parsing logic, suggesting missing sanity [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks on recursive parsing, large streams, or unbounded loops.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **PDFXrefStreamParser.java**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Replaced flat iteration over the “index” array with a nested counting loop [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat increments `entryCount` and throws if it exceeds [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mMAX_XREF_STREAM_ENTRIES[0m[39m=[0m[35m50_000[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **BaseParser.java**  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Removed the old `parseCOSDictionary` signature and inserted a new public [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that reads up to [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m MB of whitespace and throws on overflow.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **BruteForceParser.java**  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Changed a `do [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m [0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!endOfObjFound[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to a `[0m[1;35mwhile[0m[1;39m([0m[39m!endOfObjFound && [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurrentOffset<=maxScan[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to enforce the existing scan limit.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **COSParser.java**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Wrapped `[0m[1;35mparseObjectDynamically[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in a depth counter [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`parseDepth`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[33mMAX_PARSE_DEPTH[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m1000[0m[39m`, throwing if the depth is exceeded and decrementing the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounter in a `finally` block.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Compilation Log After Patch  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The build halts immediately in `BaseParser.java` at line [0m[1;36m270[0m[39m with “illegal [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstart of expression,” meaning code was inserted outside any method or class block. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `BruteForceParser.java` reports dozens of “class, interface, or enum expected”[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors, indicating that brackets are mismatched and statements now reside outside [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the class definition.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Patch Context and Braces**: Verify that inserted methods and [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol-structure changes in each file respect existing class and method [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundaries. Unbalanced `[0m[1;39m{[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` or missing method signatures appear to be the root of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe compile failures.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **BaseParser Integration**: The removal of `parseCOSDictionary` and addition [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof `[0m[1;35mskipSpaces[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` likely shifted line numbers and perhaps accidentally deleted or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcommented out braces.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **BruteForceParser Loop Replacement**: Ensure that the `do…while` to `while` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mswap preserves correct nesting of braces; the numerous subsequent errors suggest [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe loop change corrupted the class file structure.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Overall Build Hygiene**: Reapply the diff with careful alignment [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39musing `git apply --check`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to catch syntax errors before recompilation.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo assumptions about the fuzzer harness or runtime environment should be made; the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediate blocker is repairing the syntax and structure so that the codebase [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompiles cleanly.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mERROR: libFuzzer: timeout[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m275[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m276[0m[39m:     * @param isDirect indicates whether the dictionary to be read is a direct [0m [2m                [0m
